CHS is honored to announce that Crosby has been named as a 2020 District of Distinction Awardee. Over 1,000 districts statewide were eligible and only 42 met the high standard and will receive outstanding honors. Crosby will receive an outstanding honor indicating that we are in the top 4% in the state of Texas in visual art! Congrats to all of our students, campuses, and CHS leaders Ms. Gladden & Ms. Baxter! #Blessedtohavethebest #CougarPRIDE #SecondToNone #IgniteInspireImprove

Crosby High School
August 11 at 1:09 AM ·

CHS Scheduling Info:

You may now view your student schedules in Skyward. Keep in mind the following:

-The following groups may not have full schedules: New Students, Dual Credit

-New Student Logins - Please refer to an earlier post on our FB page for guidance on the new login format for students.

-Some students may be in an elective they did not choose because of the following: They may have failed to select an alternate OR the alternate did not work in their selected schedule. Also, the state (TEA) has designated programs of study for Career and Technical classes. This may have caused some student's schedules to change in order to move through a pathway and take the sequential courses within that pathway.

With these considerations, there is a schedule change request form located on the CHS webpage and on the Counselor’s site.

Here is the direct link to the form (please read it carefully). YOU MUST USE THE STUDENTS LOG IN TO ACCESS GOOGLE LINK

https://forms.gle/YkYZSm97GngWJMQE8

#CougarPride #Secondtonone

Crosby ISD
May 27 at 7:12 PM ·

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

shared_text:
Crosby ISD
May 27 at 7:15 PM ·

La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.

Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

La Transferencia Electrónica de Beneficios por Pandemia (P-EBT, por sus siglas en inglés) es un beneficio de alimentos único para las familias que perdieron el acceso a comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido debido al cierre de las escuelas. A fin de mayo, las escuelas les enviarán instrucciones para realizar una solicitud a las familias elegibles para la P-EBT. La solicitud de la P-EBT estará disponible la primera semana de junio.

Los beneficios de alimentos de la P-EBT son para los niños que recibieron beneficios de alimentos del Programa Asistencial de Nutrición Suplementaria (SNAP, por sus siglas en inglés) para marzo de 2020 y para los niños que estén certificados para recibir comidas gratuitas o a precio reducido en Texas durante el año escolar 2019-20. Para obtener más información, visite: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Please join us in congratulating Cadet Major Savannah. She will be the Commander of all cadets in school year 20-21.

Also join us in congratulating her staff: Joshua (Executive Officer), Philip (Command Sergeant Major), Mary (Human Resource), Connor (Safety / Security), James (Operations), Kyle(Logistics) and Dalton (Public Affairs).

This team will lead us through our Federal Inspection next year so congratulating them for rising to the absolute top of our program and preparing now to lead us through our Federal Inspection.

Also included in this announcement is a flashback video that highlights our year before the pandemic. Congrats to our outgoing commander of all cadets, Cadet Major Lexi Johnson.

Second to None - Never Quit even in the middle of this Pandemic Shutdown.

Crosby Jrotc added 14 new photos to the album: JROTC Shutdown? - No Way!!
March 25 at 11:52 PM ·

We are now operating 100% from our homes and using this experience as an opportunity to be positive and learn how to continue operations & learning under extreme constraints.

Sharing a few of the pictures from our cadets this week. So proud to see them doing their JROTC homework: Exercise 2-3x a week and share / send favorite exercise pictures.

We are still sorting through all of the pictures and will continue to post but beyond proud to see and post these.

Please join us in congratulating them for what they are doing. Also feel free to send more.

Second to None - Nothing Less! Never Quit!!

post_text:
Good morning,
BES and DES still have power however, the rest of the district is experiencing a power outage at this time. The power outage is being caused by a failure at the Newport electrical substation. Centerpoint estimates restoration of service by 10:30 am and will update the district as to their progress every 30 minutes. There is a possibility we may have to release everyone early and that decision will be made around 10:00 am and will be based on Centerpoint's progress.

Kevin Knight is with Michael Gonzales.
December 21, 2019 at 1:40 AM ·

I am so proud and honored to announce that the Crosby High School Band has been selected as this year’s recipient of the Sudler Flag by The John Philip Sousa Foundation! Thank you to Mr. Roy Holder and all Sudler Flag Committee members for this selection. We look forward to receiving the Flag this Spring and proudly hanging it in our band hall.

The purpose of the Sudler Flag is “to identify, recognize and honor high school band programs internationally that have demonstrated particularly significant high standards of excellence in concert activities over a period of several years.”

From our Crosby ISD Theater and Choir Department:

Cougars,

We just got permission to do one more show. We are excited about the response and many are asking for one more show to see it again or they missed it. If you have time, please come out and check it out. In the past 21 years that I have been here, this is our best show. It's the perfect storm and our company would love for everyone to see it.

Feel free to use of the photos to help us promote Godspell.

Nov. 2 - Saturday night at 7 pm

$7.00 - Adults
$5.00 - Students

post_text: Last Thursday night, the Crosby Swim Team had their first swim meet of the season vs. Summer Creek and Humble! The team did extremely well with several improved times! Stand outs include; Sophomore Emma Yates in her 50 freestyle, Junior Matthew Ashby in his 100 breaststroke and 50 freestyle, Junior Kaliegh Salge in her 100 backstroke, and Freshman Emmilee Salge in her 100 freestyle! Congrats on a good team from all relays, and competing very well against tough opponents! #CrosbyCougarPRIDE
